        "answer_count": 3,
        "title": "Combine a sequence of LineString",
        "body": "<p>I have a sequence of LineString, for example <code>lineString1<\/code> and <code>lineString2<\/code> <a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/LKgcV.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/LKgcV.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>where <code>lineString1.getEndPoint() == lineString2.getStartPoint()<\/code> or \n<code>lineString1.getStartPoint() == lineString2.getEndPoint()<\/code>\nI want to get <code>LineString<\/code> object (not <code>MultiLineString<\/code>) which would be combined of <code>lineString1<\/code> and <code>lineString2<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>I didn't find any good solution to do it.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 49883480,
